welcome to Tripoli,

01:21.448 --> 01:23.724
where the time is 8:15pm

01:23.750 --> 01:26.993
and the temperature
is a mild 82 degrees.

01:27.054 --> 01:31.662
We ask you to please be patient with
our security procedures on the ground

01:31.725 --> 01:33.500
and wish you a pleasant evening.

01:38.599 --> 01:46.074
(Electronic squealing)

01:47.941 --> 01:49.477
(Speaks in Arabic)

02:02.522 --> 02:04.126
(Speaks in Arabic)

03:17.564 --> 03:19.339
(Exhales heavily)

04:33.406 --> 04:34.942
(High-pitched whistling)

05:14.447 --> 05:17.894
Oh, please, Chuck, none of that.
I'm sorry to keep you waiting.

05:19.319 --> 05:22.857
I'm praying you've got good news for me.
How did it all go?

05:22.889 --> 05:27.565
<i>The mission to assassinate
the Libyan dictator has failed, ma'am.</i>

05:27.627 --> 05:29.129
I'm sorry.

05:30.397 --> 05:32.070
Well, that's it, then.

05:33.166 --> 05:36.204
The last roll of the dice
and it comes up snake eyes.

05:36.236 --> 05:37.806
Thank you for your efforts.

05:37.838 --> 05:40.546
It was always gonna be a long shot,
ma'am.

05:43.076 --> 05:48.424
Now that we have exhausted
your final option, Madam President,

05:48.481 --> 05:50.893
have you made a decision on mine?

05:50.917 --> 05:53.022
I have.

05:54.387 --> 05:58.927
Reluctantly,
and with a most heavy heart,

05:58.992 --> 06:04.408
I am faced with no other option but to
support your position, General Thatcher.

06:06.600 --> 06:08.511
We are going to war.

06:15.008 --> 06:20.515
